The paper deals with the problem of multiuser scheduling and power allocation in wireless communication systems with simultaneous wireless information and power transfer (SWIPT). This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) as it involves maximizing the achievable rate subject to power constraints. It also falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with the design of efficient communication protocols for wireless networks. The paper also involves optimization techniques (cs.SY) for solving non-convex optimization problems. Additionally, the paper includes simulation results (cs.MM) to demonstrate the performance gains achieved by the proposed algorithms. Finally, the paper discusses the tradeoff between system performance metrics, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG).
